The paper deals with the Fourier dimension of Boolean functions, which is a topic in computational complexity theory (cs.CC) and information theory (cs.IT). The proof method involves bounding the non-adaptive parity decision tree complexity, which is a topic in data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the paper also involves some geometric arguments, which could potentially fall under computational geometry (cs.CG).
